I love (Love) this recipe. It's so versatile. It comes out great when i bake loaves, muffins, mini muffins... Sometimes I add nuts and/or chocolate chips (divine!). I almost always use whole wheat flour, but it's just as good if you slip in quinoa or flax meal. I used creme fresh today, but think it tastes just as good if not better with sour cream or plain yogurt. And, you can even use less oil, as long as you add moisture from somewhere else (more banana, applesauce, more yogurt etc). The best part is, nobody can ever tell when they're healthy. I think the secret for their texture is the egg and sugar whipping at the beginning of this recipe. It's a keeper!

