Rating: 4
This is a great easy recipe, but I made some personalized modifications (as usual). Used 1 cup all purpose flour, 1¾ cup whole wheat and ½ cup ground flax. Used only 1¾ cups natural/demerara sugar plus two tablespoons each of honey and dark maple syrup. Added ½ teaspoon of freshly grated nutmeg. Normally I'd substitute half of the oil with applesauce, but I had none, so I used only ¾ cup of oil. The result was a deliciously moist and slightly healthier bread. I also omitted the nuts as my daughter does not like them. This recipe gave me a dozen regular sized muffins and three dozen mini muffins that will go with my daughter and her volleyball team to their regional tournment this weekend!

