Rating: 4
Ive made this recipe as stated and with different variations on oil/butter, sour cream and/ yogurt, liqueurs instead of or in addition to vanilla, chunked vs. mashed bananas, alternate garnishes, etc. All have turned out very well. The only advice I would add to that of the fabulous advice of prior reviewers is to use slightly less batter per pan than normal if using a full loaf pan, for more even cooking. Also, if you must sub kosher or sea salt for bakers salt make sure to account for the change in volume, and either grind it or dissolve it in the vanilla first. As a previous reviewer said, the mark of a good recipe is its flexibility, especially in pastry, and this recipe scales & substitutes beautifully. Some of the issues raised in the reviews sound like they are more related to pan size and/or type, oven performance (uneven temperature), or issues with ingredients (old flour, under ripe bananas, etc.) Also, the texture is on the verge of being more reminiscent of cake, so you may want to bake in muffin tins (mini muffins work great) and find a quickbread recipe for more traditionally textured banana bread.

