Rating: 4
Oh - and about the 10 minute beating of the eggs and sugar. I have tried this recipe twice just beating by hand until it thickens enough to leave "ribbons," and the bread came out fine. I've also tried using an electric hand mixer and beating it for the full 10 minutes, and I have to say -- the bread's texture turned out to be clearly superior. Not that the hand version wasn't good, but it's a bit more dense, whereas the electric 10-minute version was just very light and fluffy but still held together -- it was really amazing. Try both if you can and see.

