Rating: 3
After reading a great many of your reviews, I made this banana bread, and would only change a few things. First of all, do yourself a favor and lower the temp to 325 and cook it longer. Because there is so much sugar in this recipe (and I only used 2 cups, like many others did), the top browns too quickly. I used sour cream (instead of creme fraiche) and will next time try chcocolate chips in the batter. Unlike others that felt the banana flavor was lost on the 2nd day, that wasn't the case here, as I think that has everything to do with the bananas you choose to use and nothing to do with this recipe. Also, I think I will also try melted butter rather than oil the next time around, as it will probably have a less oily taste. All in all a good recipe, and I will definitely make it again with the aforementioned changes. Of all the reviews I have read, isn't it a riot that NOT ONE of us actually followed the recipe as printed? I love that!

