Great cake!! I made half the recipe, to accommodate the number of ripe bananas I had on hand. I also modified the recipe by using 1c whole wheat pastry flour and 1/2c all purpose flour; 1/2c white sugar and 1/2c unpacked light brown demerra (had the latter on hand and wanted to use it up); and a couple of tbls. of fromage frais (a fresh, unprocessed cream cheese) because I had neither creme fraiche nor sour cream on hand. I also added about 1/2c dark chocolate chips with the toasted walnuts. The cake was a hit: moist, tender and balanced in sweetness and flavour. The long beating of the egg with the sugar is definitely key to achieving a proper crumb with the whole meal flour. Definitely a keeper!

Rating: 4
Wonderful banana bread! I halved the recipe and now wish that I had 2 loaves. Because I had them, I used 5 medium bananas for the reduced recipe, half smashed and half sort of sliced or chunked as some reviewers suggested doing. As also suggested, I substituted and used a generous measure of sour cream, a tad more cinnamon, used half light brown sugar and half white, and then also tossed in some allspice. I was using King Arthur all purpose flour which can be a bit hard so I substituted in cake flour for a bit less than half of the flour called for altogether. I was a little concerned that it might be overly sweet as some reviewers wrote, but I only used a tad less sugar than called for thinking that if worst came to worst and the rest of the recipe was good, I could always lower the sugar significantly the next time around. I tasted the batter before putting it in the oven and it did seem pretty sweet and the cake smelled sweet when it came out to cool, but when I cut into it later, it was perfect and not overly sweet at all. I think using half brown sugar probably made all the difference. It does brown quickly so I watched it carefully after the 45 minute mark and removed it as soon as the skewer test indicated that it was done inside. It was not too dark at that point, but I could easily imagine that just a few too many extra minutes could make it so. Everyone loved it. I will definitely make this recipe again.

