One of my first attempts at banana bread and I was a bit intimidated by the earlier reviews re: excess dough and dark crust but it turned out great! I cooked the loaves in a convection oven and reduced the temp. by 5 degrees during the last half hour and they were perfect after 1 hour and 7 min. I didn't have quite 3 C of bananas so added 1 C of roughly chopped fresh cranberrys during final blending with the flour mixture, a good sweet and sour taste. I took one loaf to my office and it was gone in a 1/2 hour. Also, a big thanks to all who review the recipes on this site - I really appreciate your comments and suggestions!!

